# XIIGen Engine — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Server:** NestJS 10, TypeScript 5, Jest
- **Client:** React 18, Vite 5, Tailwind CSS, Jest + @testing-library/react
- **Infra:** Elasticsearch 8, PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7, AWS SQS (LocalStack)
- **AI:** Anthropic Claude, OpenAI, Google Gemini, xAI Grok

## Commands
```bash
cd server && npm run build          # build
cd server && npx jest --verbose     # 5,512 server tests
cd client && npx jest --verbose     # 220 client tests
docker compose up --build           # full stack
```

## Non-Negotiable Rules

### 1. Fabric First
NEVER import a provider SDK in service code. Always inject the fabric interface.
```typescript
// ✅ @Inject(DATABASE_SERVICE) private db: IDatabaseService
// ❌ import { Client } from '@elastic/elasticsearch'
```

### 2. No Typed Models (DNA-1)
ALL business data = `Record<string, unknown>`. No classes or interfaces for data.

### 3. DataProcessResult (DNA-3)
ALL service methods return `DataProcessResult<T>`. Never `throw` for business logic.

### 4. MicroserviceBase (DNA-4)
ALL services extend `MicroserviceBase`. No exceptions.

### 5. Tenant Scope (DNA-5)
Tenant is automatic via AsyncLocalStorage. NEVER pass `tenantId` as parameter.

### 6. DynamicController (DNA-6)
No entity-specific controllers (`ProductsController`, etc.).

### 7. Queue Only (Rule 11)
No HTTP between services. All inter-service communication via Queue Fabric.

### 8. Outbox Pattern (DNA-8)
`storeDocument()` MUST come BEFORE `enqueue()`.

## Directory Structure
```
server/src/
├── kernel/           ← DNA primitives (RARELY TOUCH)
├── fabrics/          ← 6 fabric layers
├── factories/        ← Factory pattern + registry
├── engine-contracts/ ← Task type definitions
├── engine/           ← Flow generator
├── guardrails/       ← BFA + DNA validator
├── freedom/          ← Config manager
├── af-stations/      ← 11 AF stations + pipeline
├── api/              ← REST controllers
└── learning/         ← Feedback + quality scoring
```

## Anti-Patterns (NEVER)
- `import { Client } from '@elastic/elasticsearch'` in service code
- `class ProductModel { name: string }` — use `Record<string, unknown>`
- `throw new Error()` for business conditions
- `tenantId` as method parameter
- Entity-specific controllers
- `fetch()` or HTTP calls between services
- `enqueue()` before `storeDocument()`
- Skip BFA validation on new flows
